Platforms

   Below are the most popular platforms for Smart TV. The full list is
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_smart_TV_platforms_and_middlewar
   e_software]here.

Samsung Tizen

Official resources

     * [http://developer.samsung.com/tv]Samsung TV Developers site - News,
       documentation and SDK downloads.
     * [https://developer.tizen.org/tizen/tv]Tizen TV Developers site -
       Full API documentation and guides for developing Tizen TV apps.
     * [https://developer.tizen.org/development/tizen-studio/download]Tize
       n Studio - IDE for TV apps development including Tizen TV Emulator.
     * [http://developer.samsung.com/tv/develop/extension-libraries/smart-
       view-sdk/download/]Smart View SDK - Official Android, IOS and
       JavaScript SDK for communication between remote device and Samsung
       Smart TV.
     * [http://developer.samsung.com/forum/?topCtgy=06]Samsung TV
       Developers Forum - Ask questions and share tips when developing
       apps with Samsung SDKs.
     * [https://samsungtvbounty.com/]Samsung Smart TV Bug Bounty - If you
       find bug in Samsung TV, submit it here and get a reward $1000+.
     * [https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=tizensdk.tizen
       tv]vscode-extension-tizentv - A Visual Studio Code extension that
       provides a lightweight IDE for Tizen application developers.

Third-party remote control libraries

     * [https://github.com/Ape/samsungctl]samsungctl - Library and command
       line tool for remote controlling Samsung televisions via a TCP/IP
       connection. It currently supports both pre-2016 TVs as well most of
       the modern Tizen-OS TVs with Ethernet or Wi-Fi connectivity
       (Python).
     * [https://github.com/Badisi/samsung-tv-remote]samsung-tv-remote -
       Node.js module to remotely control Samsung Smart TV starting from
       2016 (JavaScript).
     * [https://github.com/kyleaa/homebridge-samsungtv2016]homebridge-sams
       ungtv2016 - Plugin for
       [https://github.com/nfarina/homebridge]Homebridge that allows you
       to control your 2016 Samsung TV with HomeKit and Siri (JavaScript).

Other

     * [http://en.tab-tv.com/?page_id=7123]Identification of Samsung TV
       models 2008-2017 - How to get screen size, matrix type, year of
       development, series and ohter parameters from Samsung TV model
       name.

LG webOS

Official resources

     * [http://webostv.developer.lge.com/]webOS TV Developers Site - WebOS
       TV apps development principles, tutorials, API documentation and
       packaging tools.
     * [http://webostv.developer.lge.com/sdk/download/download-sdk/]webOS
       TV IDE + SDK - IDE for apps development including a Command Line
       Interface and emulator.
     * [http://www.svlconnectsdk.com/]Connect SDK - Open source framework
       developed by LG that connects your mobile apps with multiple media
       device platforms. Currently supports 8 platforms. But seems
       [https://github.com/ConnectSDK/Connect-SDK-Android/issues/364]aband
       oned.
     * [http://developer.lge.com/community/forums/RetrieveForumList.dev?pr
       odTypeCode=TV]webOS TV Developers Forum - Ask questions, share
       information and learn about Smart TV app development with other
       developers.

Third-party remote control libraries

     * [https://github.com/hobbyquaker/lgtv2]lgtv2 - Node.js module for
       remote control of LG webOS TV via WebSocket messages (JavaScript).
     * [https://github.com/hobbyquaker/node-red-contrib-lgtv]node-red-cont
       rib-lgtv - Module for [https://nodered.org/]Node-RED allowing
       remote control of LG webOS Smart TVs (JavaScript).
     * [https://github.com/WeeJeWel/node-webos]node-webos - Node.js module
       to discover and control webOS TVs (JavaScript).
     * [https://github.com/hobbyquaker/lgtv2mqtt]lgtv2mqtt - Interface
       between LG WebOS Smart TVs and MQTT (JavaScript).
     * [https://github.com/stevenvong/ares-webos-sdk]ares-webos-sdk -
       webOS [http://webostv.developer.lge.com/sdk/using-webos-tv-cli/]CLI
       as separate NPM module (JavaScript).
     * [https://github.com/TheRealLink/pylgtv]pylgtv - Library to control
       webOS based LG Tv devices (Python).
     * [https://github.com/klattimer/LGWebOSRemote]LGWebOSRemote - Command
       line tool for webOS remote control of LG TVs (Python).

Articles

     * [https://mym.hackpad.com/ep/pad/static/rLlshKkzdNj]LG webOS
       communication protocol - Unofficial but detailed description of
       communication endpoints of webOS TV.

Videos

     * [https://youtu.be/yxu0G7jM_us]LG Magic Motion Remote - Point,
       Click, and Control - Operate TV like a computer mouse.

Other

     * [http://openlgtv.org.ru/]openlgtv.org.ru - A non-commercial project
       for legal reverse engineering and research on LG Television
       firmware. Seems a bit outdated but contains a lot of information.
     * [http://en.tab-tv.com/?page_id=7111]Identification of LG TV models
       2011-2017 - How to get screen size, matrix type, year of
       development, series and ohter parameters from LG TV model name.

Android TV

Official resources

     * [https://developer.android.com/training/tv/start/start.html]Android
       TV Developers site - Documentation, tutorials and best practises
       for building Android TV apps.

Apple tvOS

Official resources

     * [https://developer.apple.com/tvos/]tvOS Developers Site - SDK,
       documentation and tutorials for developing tvOS apps.

Chromecast

Official resources

     * [https://developers.google.com/cast/]Google Cast SDK - Official
       Google Cast SDK documentation and tutorials.
     * [https://www.google.com/chromecast/built-in/tv/]TVs with Chromecast
       built-in - List of vendors supporting built-in Chromecast and
       advantages over traditional TV remote controller.

Cross-platform tools

     * [https://github.com/raphamorim/react-tv]react-tv - React
       development for TV: renderer for low memory applications and
       Packager for WebOS, Tizen, Orsay.
     * [http://developer.samsung.com/tv/develop/extension-libraries/toast/
       ]TOAST - Samsung open-source framework for multi-platform TV apps
       developemnt.
     * [http://enyojs.com/]Enyo - LG framework for development apps for
       all major platforms, from phones and tablets to PCs and TVs.
     * [https://github.com/immosmart/smartbox]Smartbox - Smart TV
       universal library for Samsung, LG, Philips, SmartTV Aliance, STB
       Mag app development.
     * [https://github.com/mautilus/sdk]Mautilus Smart TV SDK - A
       platform-agnostic framework for developing TV Apps. Supports
       Samsung, LG, Philips, Sony, Panasonic and VESTEL Smart TVs.

Remote control protocols

     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_Living_Network_Alliance]DLNA
       - Industry-wide standard for sharing data over a home network.
       Depending on the DLNA-compatible devices you own, you might be able
       to stream films from your laptop to your TV, play an MP3 stored on
       your phone over your hi-fi system, or print a photo from your
       tablet on your home printer.
     * [http://www.dial-multiscreen.org/]DIAL - Developed by Netflix and
       Google, this protocol alows client devices (like smartphone,
       tablet, or computer) to discover apps on server devices (like a
       smart TV or streaming box) and launch content on them.
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wi-Fi_Direct]Wi-Fi Direct - Standard
       enabling devices to easily connect with each other without
       requiring a wireless access point.
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miracast]Miracast - Standard for
       wireless connections from devices (such as laptops, tablets, or
       smartphones) to displays (such as TVs, monitors or projectors).
       Works over Wi-Fi Direct.

Misc

     * [http://lirc.org/]LIRC - A package that allows you to decode and
       send infra-red signals of many (but not all) commonly used remote
       controls.
     * [https://github.com/ruiposse/smart-tv-app-dev-guidelines]smart-tv-a
       pp-dev-guidelines - A Smart TV App Development examples, tutorials,
       best-practices and documentation. Last updated on 2015.
     * [https://github.com/linuxenko/awesome-smarttv]awesome-smarttv -
       Another list of Smart TV resources. Discovered after this one was
       already done .
     * [https://github.com/stuart-williams/lrud]lrud - Left, Right, Up,
       Down. A spatial navigation library for devices with input via
       directional controls.

Community

     * [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/smart-tv]Stack Overflow
     * [https://www.reddit.com/r/smarttv]Reddit

Contribute

   Feel free to share your experience and contribute useful extension
   resources by creating
   [https://github.com/vitalets/awesome-smart-tv/issues]new issue or
   [https://github.com/vitalets/awesome-smart-tv/pulls]pull request.
   Please read the
   [file://localhost/vitalets/awesome-smart-tv/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md
   ]contribution guidelines first. Thanks!

